column5: Gonna be another gorgeous day !!  If your fish'n today, good luck,  If your goin to work today, I'm sorry to hear that.
morning  no fishing or work today..well no paid work have things to do around the house

Good morning Lew. It does look like another beautiful day shaping up I am fortunate to wake up at the cottage everyday. but still need to go to work today. Next week off on holidays to get a little fishing in.
Good morning all.  I just came in from taking Brook for a walk, it is a beauty day.  I have work, but it's at home work at my leisure.
Good morning guys. Hope you all have a great day whatever you're doing.
Good morning gentlemen. I'm looking forward to work today... I need a break from the projects I've been tackling at home.  Have a good one!
Just heading out shortly for the first day back after a week off...it's gonna be a long day.
it's a beautiful morning. The sun is shining, the dogs are happy and the home is filled with the aroma of fresh brewed and bacon.
I was going to go fishing today, but my car broke down..... (actually it is expensive enough to have malfunctioned).
Good morning, was gonna go to work, but my 30 Gallon fish tank decided to spring a leak last night...so, not fishing but am working on my fishes home?  Maureen
Morning all, definitely a beautiful day.  Maureen, sorry to hear about the tank, had it happen with my 30 many years ago...what a mess.  HTHM, get that car fixed, the boat is ready to go lol
Good morning all. Have a great day everyone..
Just back from the dentist and then into work this afternoon.  So I got it in the MOUTH this AM and I'll get it in the REAR this afternoon  Good morning all and thx for the picture Lew.
Lew, I don't think you're sorry at ALL!!     And Maureen...I've got a 30 gallon tank that's taking up space...seriously...pm me if your leaks don't get fixed

Morning!! I am off today, but doing garden work. I just returned form a week at a Kawartha Lake that starts with a "C" and is between Sturgeon and Balsam lakes. But in the new era of conservation and confidentiality, I don't want to say more than that. The fishing was really quite good and next week we are off to "Big (the name of a female deer, but I can't say more than that)". Have a good day all! Jim
